{"id":798677,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Network_(1976_movie)","text":"\"Network\" is a 1976 American satirical black comedy-drama movie written by Paddy Chayefsky and directed by Sidney Lumet. It is about a fictional television network, UBS, and its struggle with poor ratings. The movie stars Faye Dunaway, William Holden, Peter Finch and Robert Duvall with Wesley Addy, Ned Beatty and Beatrice Straight.\n\"Network\" had strong positive reviews. It won four Academy Awards, in the categories of Best Actor (Finch), Best Actress (Dunaway), Best Supporting Actress (Straight) and Best Original Screenplay (Chayefsky).","categories":[],"infobox_types":["film"],"annotations":[{"uri":"Satire","surface_form":"satirical","offset":29},{"uri":"Black_comedy","surface_form":"black comedy","offset":39},{"uri":"Drama","surface_form":"drama","offset":52},{"uri":"Paddy_Chayefsky","surface_form":"Paddy Chayefsky","offset":75},{"uri":"Sidney_Lumet","surface_form":"Sidney Lumet","offset":107},{"uri":"Television_network","surface_form":"television network","offset":145},{"uri":"Audience_measurement","surface_form":"ratings","offset":197},{"uri":"Faye_Dunaway","surface_form":"Faye Dunaway","offset":222},{"uri":"William_Holden","surface_form":"William Holden","offset":236},{"uri":"Peter_Finch","surface_form":"Peter Finch","offset":252},{"uri":"Robert_Duvall","surface_form":"Robert Duvall","offset":268},{"uri":"Wesley_Addy","surface_form":"Wesley Addy","offset":287},{"uri":"Ned_Beatty","surface_form":"Ned Beatty","offset":300},{"uri":"Beatrice_Straight","surface_form":"Beatrice Straight","offset":315},{"uri":"Academy_Awards","surface_form":"Academy Awards","offset":385},{"uri":"Academy_Award_for_Best_Actor","surface_form":"Best Actor","offset":422},{"uri":"Academy_Award_for_Best_Actress","surface_form":"Best Actress","offset":442},{"uri":"Academy_Award_for_Best_Supporting_Actress","surface_form":"Best Supporting Actress","offset":466},{"uri":"Academy_Award_for_Best_Original_Screenplay